      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented evidence that simulation setup, boundary condition application, and post-processing are performed by qualified personnel following written procedures with independent review.",
      "rationale": "Use error factor was not formally assessed. No written simulation execution procedures or independent review records were provided. Flagged as an epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty for the hemolysis power-law correlation and turbulence model must be quantified and shown to be acceptable for absolute hemolysis prediction at MRL 5.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty was not assessed. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is known to have significant model form uncertainty for absolute predictions, but no formal assessment was conducted. This is a critical epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
